;; EM-2 (edge-matrix, 2026-07-02): quoted symbols inside a guard clause
;; result (and in the raise argument) are parsed as VARIABLE references,
;; not quoted data: "Undefined variable: c" / "Undefined variable: boom".
;; Works when the guard expression is a bare top-level display operand
;; WITHOUT the quote in the clause (e.g. numeric results are fine).
;;
;; Found by: pair099_guard_raise__tail_position et al. (guard_raise_
;; catch_sym__in__*): compile errors, then edge-chk arity-shift cascade.
;;
;; Expected output:  c
;; Actual:           error: Undefined variable: c   (JIT and AOT)
(display (guard (e (#t 'c)) 42)) (newline)
